The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | NTPC fined for landgrab minus job
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           NTPC fined for landgrab minus job
                            
	New Delhi, June 18 (PTI): The Central Information Commission has asked the National Thermal Power Corporation to pay Rs 11.28 lakh to an oustee for denying him a job at the Farakka power project.         
	The transparency panel also directed the power major to explore ways of redressing grievances of farmers who were rendered landless because of the project.        
	The NTPC is required to pay a compensation for all kinds of losses and other detriment suffered by the oustee in the process of securing justice through different ways... including his claim for the right to work, information commissioner M.M. Ansari said.        
	The panel directed the public sector company to pay the money to Murshidabad resident Mohd Samad Khan whose land, along with that of 42 others, was acquired in 1980s for the project in Bengal.                                                                                                                                                                                     
